title: The Bachelorette: Angie Kent's finalist Jackson Garlick spotted partying in Cabo
text:
The Bachelorette's Jackson Garlick was spotted partying alongside several bikini-clad women in Cabo this week, suggesting he does not win the show.

Rugby player Jackson, 25, who makes it to Angie's final four, is in Mexico celebrating his father, and former Rabbitohs player, Sean Garlick's 50th birthday.

On Sunday, The Daily Telegraph published photographs of Jackson at a wild boat party alongside Sam Burgess and many stunning women.

Spoiler! The Bachelorette's Jackson Garlick (pictured) was spotted partying alongside several bikini-clad women in Cabo this week, suggesting he does not win the show

If Jackson had won the dating show, he would likely be keeping a much lower profile while being careful not to be photographed around other women.

One of the women partying alongside Jackson on the boat was brunette Ashley Olsen, who he previously shared a selfie with in November, 2018.

Ashley shared footage from the boat of several girls dancing on the shoulders of three men, with Sam Burgess appearing in high spirits.

Family! Rugby player Jackson (right), who makes it to Angie's final four, is in Mexico celebrating his father, and former Rabbitohs player, Sean Garlick's (left) 50th birthday

History? One of the women Jackson partied alongside at a boat party was brunette Ashley Olsen (left), who he previously shared a selfie with in November, 2018

Despite being the youngest suitor on The Bachelorette, Jackson has already proved to be one of the favourites to win Angie's heart.

Earlier this month, she chose him for a single date and the pair took to the skies in a helicopter.

But things didn't go to plan when Angie, 29, began suffering from motion sickness.

Wild! Ashley shared footage from the boat of several girls dancing on the shoulders of three men, with Sam Burgess (centre) also in attendance and appearing in high-spirits

What will Angie Kent say? If Jackson had won the dating show, he would be keeping a much lower profile while careful not to be photographed around other women

'You can spew in my top pocket if you want,' he said, with Angie telling him, 'That would be the worst thing ever!'

Despite Angie saying the date was a 'disaster', Jackson assured her it was okay and he was eventually rewarded with a rose.

Last week, Daily Mail Australia published exclusive pictures showing Jackson makes it to Angie's final four, alongside Timm Hanley, Carlin Sterritt and Ryan Anderson.
